events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 33 points and nine assists and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Detroit Pistons 124-101 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trail Blazers beat Pistons 124-101 for 4th straight win

headlines.description: — Duncan Robinson and Jimmy Butler helped Miami rally from a 13-point first-half deficit by spurring a decisive eight-point fourth-quarter run to give the Heat a 92-87 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat turns up defensive pressure in 92-87 win at Indiana

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 36 points and eight rebounds and the Dallas Mavericks held on to beat the Boston Celtics 113-108 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic's scores 36, leads Mavericks past Celtics 113-108

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving had 31 points and a season-high 12 assists, and the Brooklyn Nets overcame the loss of James Harden to beat the Houston Rockets 120-108 on Wednesday night and move into first place in the Eastern Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets lose Harden but beat Rockets, move into first in East

headlines.description: — Mike Conley scored 13 of his 26 points in the fourth quarter, Jordan Clarkson added 24 points and the Utah Jazz beat the Memphis Grizzlies 111-107 on Wednesday night for their seventh straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Conley's fourth quarter leads Jazz past Grizzlies 111-107

events.name: New York Knicks at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 11 of his 24 points over the final eight minutes, leading a fierce rally by the Minnesota Timberwolves for a 102-101 victory over former coach Tom Thibodeau and the New York Knicks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards leads Timberwolves' rally past Thibs, Knicks 102-101

events.name: Toronto Raptors at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Svi Mykhailiuk scored 10 of his season-high 22 points in the fourth quarter, and the Oklahoma City Thunder rallied to beat the Toronto Raptors 113-103 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oklahoma City tops Raptors 113-103, snaps 3-game skid

events.name: Sacramento Kings at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 26 points and the San Antonio Spurs snapped Sacramento’s five-game winning streak, beating the Kings 120-106 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs beat Sacramento 120-105, end Kings' 5-game win streak

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Andre Drummond left his Lakers debut with a bruised right toe, and Jrue Holiday scored 28 points in the Milwaukee Bucks' 112-97 victory over Los Angeles on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Drummond leaves debut with bruised toe, Bucks beat LA 112-97

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored a season-high 45 points, Chris Paul added 19 points and 14 assists, and the Phoenix Suns held on to beat the Chicago Bulls 121-116 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores season-high 45, Suns beat Bulls 121-116
